  'An 8.5-hour Busan-departure shuttle tour to Gyeongju''s biggest spring cherry blossom spots. The default route covers Bomun Lake (8 km of cherry tree-lined lakeside walking), the Cheomseongdae + Daereungwon historic core (UNESCO Gyeongju Historic Areas), and Bulguksa Temple (UNESCO World Heritage with mid-April yaezakura double cherry blossom). 2–3 stops are confirmed each morning based on the day''s bloom report. Tour operates Mar 28 to Apr 10 only — full refund if bloom is materially delayed or finished.',
